726464f-a.title: Queens: Cypress Hills Street - Fresh Pond Road
726464f-a.text:
Cypress Hills Street (foreground), between Fresh Pond Road (left)
and 64th Street (rioht). This is a set of two views showing the rear of
two homes facing on Fresh Pond Road. At the extremes of view No. 1 are the
homes of Edsall and Henry W. Meyer respectively. The home of Henry W.
Meyer (right) is now the 116th Precinct Police and Station house.
March 1923.
View 2: 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726729f-b.title: Queens: Fresh Pond Road - Cypress Hills Street
726729f-b.text:
Fresh Pond Road, east side, north of Cypress Hills St., and Catalpa
Ave., showing the home of Philip Edaall. Mrs. Edsall was the owner in
1852. This house does not appear in 1929.
March 1922.
View 2: 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
